The paper deals with the secrecy capacity of a multiple-input and multiple-output (MIMO) broadcast channel with confidential messages (BCC) and delayed channel state information (CSI). This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), and multimedia (cs.MM). However, given the focus on channel capacity and information transmission, cs.IT is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.CR for the security aspect. The other sub-categories are also relevant but to a lesser extent.
